  <prompt>Audit `infrastructure/bicep/modules/redis.bicep`. Verify required parameters per FR-09: `name`, `location`, `sku` (object: name/family/capacity), `minimumTlsVersion` (default "1.2"), `enableNonSslPort` (default false), `redisVersion`, optional `vnetSubnetId`, optional `staticIP`, optional `tags`. Outputs: `name`, `hostName`, `sslPort`, resource ID, primary key. Add any missing parameter/output (extend; do not duplicate module). Exploration finding: current SKU param is a string + capacity int (not an object). Decide whether to migrate to object form OR document why string+int satisfies FR-09.</prompt>
  <role>Spaarke infrastructure developer with Bicep familiarity.</role>
  <goal>`redis.bicep` parameter surface complete per FR-09 list. Decision documented if SKU parameterization shape diverges from spec's "object" expectation.</goal>
  <context><background>Spec describes SKU as object; current module uses string + int (per exploration). Both shapes can satisfy SKU configuration. Document the decision.</background><relevant-files><file>infrastructure/bicep/modules/redis.bicep</file></relevant-files></context>
  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec">FR-09 â€” extend, don't duplicate.</constraint>
    <constraint source="azure-deployment.md">Idempotent deploy.</constraint>
  </constraints>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-redis-cache-remediation-r1/spec.md</file>
