    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read current `redis.bicep`. Enumerate parameters + outputs.</step>
    <step order="2">Compare against FR-09 list. Identify gaps.</step>
    <step order="3">If SKU is currently string+int and spec calls for object: evaluate impact. Decide: (a) refactor to object (preferred per spec); (b) keep string+int and document rationale (acceptable if it satisfies all use cases).</step>
    <step order="4">Add any missing parameter (e.g., `staticIP`, `vnetSubnetId`, `tags` if not present).</step>
    <step order="5">Verify outputs include `name`, `hostName`, `sslPort`, resource ID, primary key.</step>
    <step order="6">`bicep build redis.bicep` â€” verify compiles.</step>
    <step order="7">Document decision in `notes/redis-bicep-audit.md`.</step>
    <step order="8">Update TASK-INDEX + current-task.</step>
  </steps>
  <tools><tool name="Read">redis.bicep</tool><tool name="Edit">Module modifications</tool><tool name="Bash">bicep build</tool><tool name="Write">audit notes</tool></tools>
